The paper discusses the need for uncertainty-aware AI/ML systems for decision support, which falls under the category of AI and machine learning (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the challenges and research directions for uncertainty-aware AI/ML systems, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper provides a theoretical demonstration of integrating two emerging uncertainty-aware ML and AI technologies, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
